{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idf6c91c43-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s51510"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"51510"},"text":"§ 51510.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Deferment of service obligation under student incentive payment agreements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of Transportation may defer the service commitment of an individual under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s51509/d/5"},"text":"section 51509(d)(5) of this title","children":[],"tail":" (as specified in the agreement under section 51509) for not more than 2 years if the individual is engaged in a graduate course of study approved by the Secretary. However, deferment of service as a commissioned officer on active duty must be approved by the Secretary of the affected military department (or the Secretary of Commerce, for service with the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idf6c91c44-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304/s8/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–304, § 8(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-06"},"text":"Oct. 6, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/1581"},"text":"120 Stat. 1581","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idf6c91c45-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idf6c91c46-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idf6c91c47-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"t